(13, 1, '2022-05-26 10:50:30', '2022-05-26 10:50:30', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>CCTO:<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://forum.netgate.com/topic/134042/sg-1000-stuck-in-boot-loop-after-initial-configuration/2\" target=\"_blank\">https://forum.netgate.com/topic/134042/sg-1000-stuck-in-boot-loop-after-initial-configuration/2</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>a. Open Putty application and follow the settings in pre-requisite section below.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>b. Once you successfully connected follow the steps below:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>At the console press any key to interrupt the boot loader when you see:<br><code>Hit [Enter] to boot immediately, or any other key for command prompt.</code><br>At the prompt enter: boot -s<br>That will boot in single user mode to a question asking for a path to the shell, just press return to reach the # prompt.</li><li>At the # prompt run the following command:<br>/sbin/fsck -y /</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Run the fsck command at least 6 times; Repeat the command until no errors are reported, even if fsck claims the filesystem has been marked \"clean\".</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true,\"start\":3} -->\n<ol start=\"3\"><li>Reboot by running: /sbin/rebootThe fastert way to get you back up and running is to re-install.</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That should do it but if it\'s a larger filesystem issue, fastest way to get you back up and running is to re-install. Here\'s how to do that<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://www.netgate.com/docs/pfsense/solutions/sg-1000/reinstall-pfsense.html\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.netgate.com/docs/pfsense/solutions/sg-1000/reinstall-pfsense.html</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>PRE-REQUISITE:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.netgate.com/pfsense/en/latest/solutions/sg-1000/connect-to-console.html\">https://docs.netgate.com/pfsense/en/latest/solutions/sg-1000/connect-to-console.html</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>PuTTY in Windows</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Open PuTTY and select&nbsp;Session&nbsp;under&nbsp;Category&nbsp;on the left hand side. Next, set the&nbsp;Connection type&nbsp;to&nbsp;Serial. Then, set&nbsp;Serial line&nbsp;to the console port that was located above, in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://docs.netgate.com/pfsense/en/latest/solutions/sg-1000/connect-to-console.html#locate-the-console-port-device\">Locate the Console Port Device</a>, and the&nbsp;Speed&nbsp;to&nbsp;<code>115200</code>&nbsp;bits per second.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Click the&nbsp;Open&nbsp;button and the console screen will be displayed.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><img src=\"https://docs.netgate.com/pfsense/en/latest/solutions/_images/putty1.png\" alt=\"../_images/putty1.png\"></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>An example of using PuTTY in Windows.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>PuTTY in Linux</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Open PuTTY from a terminal by typing&nbsp;sudo putty. Next, set the&nbsp;Connection type&nbsp;to&nbsp;Serial. Then, set&nbsp;Serial line&nbsp;to&nbsp;/dev/ttyUSB0&nbsp;and the&nbsp;Speed&nbsp;to&nbsp;<code>115200</code>&nbsp;bits per second.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Click the&nbsp;Open&nbsp;button and the console screen will be displayed.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><img src=\"https://docs.netgate.com/pfsense/en/latest/solutions/_images/putty-linux.jpg\" alt=\"../_images/putty-linux.jpg\"></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>An example of using PuTTY in Linux.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>GNU screen</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In many cases&nbsp;<code>screen</code>&nbsp;may be invoked simply by using the proper command line, where&nbsp;<code>&lt;console-port&gt;</code>&nbsp;is the console port that was located above.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:preformatted -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">sudo screen &lt;console-port&gt; 115200\n</pre>\n<!-- /wp:preformatted -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If portions of the text are unreadable but appear to be properly formatted, the most likely culprit is a character encoding mismatch in the terminal. Adding the&nbsp;<code>-U</code>&nbsp;parameter to the&nbsp;<code>screen</code>&nbsp;command line arguments forces it to use UTF-8 for character encoding:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:preformatted -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">sudo screen -U &lt;console-port&gt; 115200\n</pre>\n<!-- /wp:preformatted -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Terminal Settings</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The settings to use within the terminal program are:Speed</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>115200 baud, the speed of the BIOSData bits</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>8Parity</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>noneStop bits</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>1Flow Control</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Off&nbsp;or&nbsp;XON/OFF. Hardware flow control (RTS/CTS) must be&nbsp;disabl</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Netgate pfSense SG-110 stuck in boot loop', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'netgate-pfsense-sg-110-stuck-in-boot-loop', '', '', '2022-05-26 10:50:30', '2022-05-26 10:50:30', '', 0, 'http://localhost/nosystems-online/?p=13', 0, 'post', '', 0),
